$13 {with a very complicated position.}) 15... Nxf6 16. Nd2 {[#] Now we can
see the point behind 13.a4. Black still has some problems to solve since his
c4-pawn is hanging.} (16. Qxa7 {is a bit better with the pawn on a4, but still
allows Black to take over the initiative with} Bc5 17. Qa6 O-O $132) {Here,
Black has two reasonable ways to try to solve his opening problems in the most
active way. Firstly, we can borrow the idea from 9.Qc3 line:} 16... Qb6 $5 {
The queen trade relieves the pressure off the c4 pawn.} ({Black can also play
