Qe5 Qf6 21. Qxf6 gxf6 22. bxc3 f5 $13) 18... bxc3 19. Ne4 Nxe4 20. Bxe4 {
when the following pawn sacrifice:} Bc6 21. Qg4 Bxe4 $1 22. Qxe6+ Be7 23. Qxe4
O-O $44 {[#] gives him a good compensation for a pawn. His c-passer is very
strong.}) 17. Qxb6 (17. Qf4 {does not change much} Qc7 $11) 17... axb6 18. a5 (
{Alternatives are harmless, for instance:} 18. Nf3 c3 19. bxc3 bxc3 20. Ba3
Bxa3 21. Rxa3 Ke7 22. Rc1 Rhd8 $11) 18... bxa5 19. Rxa5 {White is more active
and better developed, but Black has a strong asset on the queenside. Here I
